<h1>The Highwaymen</h1>

<p>Ken Auletta<br>
High points digested by A. Fox</p>

<p>Index: 

<ul>
  <li><a href="#diller">Diller Peeks Into the Future</a></li>
  <li><a href="#cowboy">The Cowboy</a></li>
</ul>

<h3><a name="diller"></a>Diller Peeks Into the Future</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Be in the broader business.&nbsp; Communication, not the Web; entertainment provision,
    not producing a show; etc.</li>
  <li>Diller had surprisingly good vision (for a non-techie) of how to marry technology to a
    sales story.&nbsp; This is a rare ability.</li>
  <li>Technologists are insular.&nbsp; Don't trust them (necessarily) to produce the
    vision/application from the technology.</li>
</ul>

<h3><a name="cowboy"></a>The Cowboy</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Companies have permanent interests, not permanent allies (or permanent personal friends;
    an unfortunate casualty of being in the business--ugh)</li>
  <li>Family matters.</li>
  <li>&quot;The only thing more fickle than technology is the opinion of the herd.&quot;</li>
</ul>

